ncertainty is statistical and second systematic. This result is\ncompatible with the larger of the theoretical predictions that connect models\nof hyperon decays using partially conserved axial currents and SU(3) symmetry\nwith those involving the heavy-quark expansion and heavy-quark symmetry. In\naddition, the branching fraction of the normalization channel,\n${\\cal{B}}(\\Xi_c^+\\to p K^- \\pi^+) = (1.135 \\pm 0.002 \\pm 0.387)$% is measured.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Jul 2020 16:00:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 11 Sep 2020 13:11:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-21"}
