round model as\na nuisance parameter and marginalizing over it, still recovers unbiased results\nbut at the expense of much larger errors ($f_\\text{NL} =\n0.75^{+40.2}_{-44.5}$), that can only be reduced by imposing the Planck 2018\nprior. Our results show that significant progress on understanding and\ncontrolling foreground removal effects is necessary in order to study PNG with\nHI intensity mapping.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Jul 2020 16:54:39 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 Oct 2020 10:07:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-20"}
